prompt: Can patients whit metformin present swollen ankles
response: It is possible for patients taking metformin to present with symptoms of peripheral edema, such as swollen ankles. However, this symptom can also be seen in other conditions or as a side effect of other medications. To determine if metformin is the cause, further evaluation and assessment are necessary. It is recommended to consult with a healthcare professional for a thorough examination and appropriate management.
